<item>
<title><![CDATA[For most new parents, bringing a child into the world is one of ...]]></title>
<link>https://prank-arum.github.io/Feeds/TikTok/caylaclark8/7583852795002916127.mp4</link>
<guid>https://tiktok.com/embed/7583852795002916127</guid>
<description>
<![CDATA[For most new parents, bringing a child into the world is one of the happiest moments of their lives. But in the U.S., it often comes with confusing billing codes, surprise charges, and a healthcare system that feels impossible to navigate, turning what should be pure joy into long-term stress and unexpected financial strain. Childbirth is now the most common reason for hospitalization in America, yet families regularly face bills they never agreed to and costs they never saw coming. In fact, almost 1 in 5 insured mothers receives a surprise medical bill after giving birth, and prices for a routine, uncomplicated delivery can range from $5,000 to over $30,000, depending on the hospital. That lack of transparency isn’t just frustrating. It’s destabilizing. When we talk about stronger families, we can’t overlook the real experiences of mothers navigating a system that’s larger, more expensive, and less transparent than it needs to be. A healthcare system should make people feel supported, not confused and overwhelmed.<br>#maternalhealth
#motherhood
#newmom
<img src="https://p16-common-sign.tiktokcdn-us.com/tos-useast8-p-0068-tx2/oUUGojrwIhZGQgLAkJgAhQoe9EpGF7RffQQ0fz~tplv-tiktokx-origin.image?dr=9636&amp;x-expires=1768226400&amp;x-signature=oGbJxOPfClxFNeTw9lvhwlBmXrg%3D&amp;t=4d5b0474&amp;ps=13740610&amp;shp=81f88b70&amp;shcp=43f4a2f9&amp;idc=useast8" /><br><a href="https://tiktok.com/@caylaclark8/video/7583852795002916127">FULL POST</a> | <a href="https://tiktok.com/embed/7583852795002916127">EMBED</a> | <a href="https://ezgif.com/rotate-video?url=https://prank-arum.github.io/Feeds/TikTok/caylaclark8/7583852795002916127.mp4">REVERSED</a><br>]]>
